Well, inside here we're going to do

00:04:30.140 --> 00:04:32.705
the exact same thing we looked at in the console.

00:04:32.705 --> 00:04:35.450
We will first select the document.

00:04:35.450 --> 00:04:38.510
The document is this full HTML document

00:04:38.510 --> 00:04:40.060
which we are currently working in.

00:04:40.060 --> 00:04:43.280
It's going to select this and then we need to filter

00:04:43.280 --> 00:04:44.810
down these documents to

00:04:44.810 --> 00:04:47.615
the particular element which we want to select.

00:04:47.615 --> 00:04:52.655
Remember we looked at a method called get elements by ID.

00:04:52.655 --> 00:04:54.365
Again, this is CamelCase.

00:04:54.365 --> 00:04:57.215
Each and every word after the first one begins with

00:04:57.215 --> 00:05:00.450
a capital inside the brackets,

00:05:00.450 --> 00:05:02.570
and the quotations will then pass in

00:05:02.570 --> 00:05:05.060
a unique ID which you want to select.

00:05:05.060 --> 00:05:08.315
In our case, we're going to grab the title.

00:05:08.315 --> 00:05:10.400
Move this into here.

00:05:10.400 --> 00:05:13.310
We looked at changing the inner contents or

00:05:13.310 --> 00:05:17.265
the inner text of this element with.innertext.

00:05:17.265 --> 00:05:20.240
This is a property where we can add a new text string

00:05:20.240 --> 00:05:23.090
in between the single or the double quotations.

00:05:23.090 --> 00:05:25.070
Let's just change this to JavaScript for

00:05:25.070 --> 00:05:27.660
now and save this file.

00:05:27.660 --> 00:05:30.485
Then if we go over to the browser and reload,

00:05:30.485 --> 00:05:32.690
this has now selected our level 1

00:05:32.690 --> 00:05:35.935
heading and changed the inner HTML.

