An alert is a pop-up inside the browser.

00:06:44.330 --> 00:06:48.630
Let's just add this with the text of clicked.

00:06:48.630 --> 00:06:51.615
Give this a save and refresh the browser.

00:06:51.615 --> 00:06:54.485
Move the mouse over to the elements and click.

00:06:54.485 --> 00:06:56.995
I will now see a page alert.

00:06:56.995 --> 00:06:58.760
This is probably something which you've

00:06:58.760 --> 00:07:00.650
seen when browsing the web in the past.

00:07:00.650 --> 00:07:03.560
All we need to do to remove this is to click on

00:07:03.560 --> 00:07:05.480
the Okay button and this will then be

00:07:05.480 --> 00:07:07.965
closed. Let's just remove this.

00:07:07.965 --> 00:07:10.460
Also just be aware that it is generally

00:07:10.460 --> 00:07:13.040
discouraged to keep our JavaScript in

00:07:13.040 --> 00:07:16.520
line just like this because it mixes up our HTML and

00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:18.140
our JavaScript and makes

00:07:18.140 --> 00:07:20.590
things less readable and organized.

00:07:20.590 --> 00:07:22.910
If possible, keep it all separate,

00:07:22.910 --> 00:07:23.980
just like we have here,

00:07:23.980 --> 00:07:25.610
and we'll also look at how we can add this

00:07:25.610 --> 00:07:28.595
into a separate file in just a moment.

00:07:28.595 --> 00:07:31.400
This is contained inside of a script tag and

00:07:31.400 --> 00:07:34.100
we can add as many script tags as you want.

00:07:34.100 --> 00:07:37.565
It could also be located anywhere on this page too,

00:07:37.565 --> 00:07:40.610
including up inside of the head section.

00:07:40.610 --> 00:07:43.490
This works in exactly the same way if we grab all of

00:07:43.490 --> 00:07:45.680
this script section and then

00:07:45.680 --> 00:07:49.105
Command or Control X to cut this out of place.

00:07:49.105 --> 00:07:50.570
Place this inside of

00:07:50.570 --> 00:07:52.220
the head section with command or control

00:07:52.220 --> 00:07:55.655
V to paste this in and also the browser.

00:07:55.655 --> 00:07:56.870
Inside here we can see

00:07:56.870 --> 00:08:00.535
the original page title is reinstated.

00:08:00.535 --> 00:08:02.255
Now since we've moved

00:08:02.255 --> 00:08:03.995
the script tag up to the head section,

00:08:03.995 --> 00:08:06.860
none of this JavaScript seems to be applying.

00:08:06.860 --> 00:08:08.630
So let's take a look inside

00:08:08.630 --> 00:08:11.345
the console and see if we can spot any errors.

00:08:11.345 --> 00:08:13.950
Right-click and inspect.

00:08:14.240 --> 00:08:17.340
Click on the Console tab at the top.

00:08:17.340 --> 00:08:21.550
We see we cannot set the property innertext of null.

00:08:21.550 --> 00:08:23.210
When we do get an error, it's

00:08:23.210 --> 00:08:24.920
often a good idea to head into

00:08:24.920 --> 00:08:26.510
the console and it will often give us

00:08:26.510 --> 00:08:29.375
a pointer to exactly what the problem is.

00:08:29.375 --> 00:08:31.250
The current problem is caused because

00:08:31.250 --> 00:08:35.240
HTML page is loaded from top to bottom.

00:08:35.240 --> 00:08:38.630
So the script inside of the head section is loaded before

00:08:38.630 --> 00:08:41.914
it even knows this title element exists,

00:08:41.914 --> 00:08:43.970
which is then causing an error.

00:08:43.970 --> 00:08:45.920
If we do need to add a script

00:08:45.920 --> 00:08:47.630
inside the head section like this,

00:08:47.630 --> 00:08:49.580
it can often cause problems if we need to

00:08:49.580 --> 00:08:52.150
access any of our DOM elements.

00:08:52.150 --> 00:08:54.050
This is why we often see JavaScript

00:08:54.050 --> 00:08:55.805
at the end of the body section.

00:08:55.805 --> 00:08:58.490
It allows the elements to be loaded fast and

00:08:58.490 --> 00:09:01.775
doesn't block the HTML from loading onto the page.

00:09:01.775 --> 00:09:02.870
You will, however,

00:09:02.870 --> 00:09:05.375
see some third-party JavaScript libraries

00:09:05.375 --> 00:09:06.560
which need the script to be

00:09:06.560 --> 00:09:08.720
loaded inside the head section

00:09:08.720 --> 00:09:11.315
for the library to function correctly.

00:09:11.315 --> 00:09:13.385
Also, these third-party libraries,

00:09:13.385 --> 00:09:14.780
along with our own code,

00:09:14.780 --> 00:09:18.685
is usually separated into its own script file.

00:09:18.685 --> 00:09:22.280
Moving all of this JavaScript into its own file will make

00:09:22.280 --> 00:09:26.430
this HTML documents much more readable and maintainable.

00:09:26.430 --> 00:09:29.465
To do this first, open up the sidebar

00:09:29.465 --> 00:09:33.130
and then inside of the where to add JavaScript folder,

00:09:33.130 --> 00:09:35.200
click on the new file icon,

00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:37.665
and then we can give this a name of our choice.

00:09:37.665 --> 00:09:39.775
I'm going to go for script 1.

00:09:39.775 --> 00:09:44.895
Then it needs to have the dot js extension. Hit Enter.

00:09:44.895 --> 00:09:46.620
Back into our index page,

00:09:46.620 --> 00:09:49.990
we can copy the contents between the script tags.

00:09:49.990 --> 00:09:54.545
Grab these two lines of code, put these outs.

00:09:54.545 --> 00:09:57.985
Paste these into our new script file.

00:09:57.985 --> 00:09:59.710
This script file doesn't need

00:09:59.710 --> 00:10:01.930
the surrounding script tags since we

00:10:01.930 --> 00:10:03.700
already know this is a JavaScript file

00:10:03.700 --> 00:10:06.070
from the dot js extension.

00:10:06.070 --> 00:10:07.825
But what we do need to do is to

00:10:07.825 --> 00:10:09.895
link these two files together.

00:10:09.895 --> 00:10:12.290
Currently, these are two separate files

00:10:12.290 --> 00:10:13.925
independent of each other.

00:10:13.925 --> 00:10:15.380
Over in the index file,

00:10:15.380 --> 00:10:18.050
we need to point to this new script file.

00:10:18.050 --> 00:10:21.410
We can do this inside of the script tags rather

00:10:21.410 --> 00:10:24.695
than having the code located inside like we did before.

00:10:24.695 --> 00:10:28.205
What we can do is to add the source attributes.

00:10:28.205 --> 00:10:30.620
The source attribute is basically

00:10:30.620 --> 00:10:33.110
the location of this file

00:10:33.110 --> 00:10:35.995
relative to where we currently are.

00:10:35.995 --> 00:10:39.890
This works exactly the same as adding a style sheet.

00:10:39.890 --> 00:10:41.990
Since this file is alongside each other,

00:10:41.990 --> 00:10:46.399
we can point to this with the source of script 1 dot js.

00:10:46.399 --> 00:10:48.560
If this was located inside of

00:10:48.560 --> 00:10:50.360
a JavaScript folder, for example,

00:10:50.360 --> 00:10:51.740
we'll need to go into

00:10:51.740 --> 00:10:53.540
the JavaScript folder and then

00:10:53.540 --> 00:10:56.170
forward slash into our script.

00:10:56.170 --> 00:11:00.125
We don't have this, so it's simply script one dot js.

00:11:00.125 --> 00:11:02.450
Make sure both of our files are saved and

00:11:02.450 --> 00:11:05.075
then over to the browser, refresh.

00:11:05.075 --> 00:11:08.005
we see the same issue inside the browser.

00:11:08.005 --> 00:11:11.520
We can not set the property innertext of null.

00:11:11.520 --> 00:11:14.060
This makes sense because we are still loading up

00:11:14.060 --> 00:11:16.655
the script tag inside of the head section.

00:11:16.655 --> 00:11:18.260
We're trying to apply this to

00:11:18.260 --> 00:11:20.945
an element before it's even been loaded.

00:11:20.945 --> 00:11:23.030
We could write some custom code to

00:11:23.030 --> 00:11:24.950
wait for the HTML to load first

00:11:24.950 --> 00:11:26.060
or we can look at

00:11:26.060 --> 00:11:29.790
some more modern techniques in the upcoming video.
